  <front>
   <head>Written for my Son to his Master, on the Anniversary of the Battle of the Boyne.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">what we owe great  then</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Forgotten by ungrateful Men?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And has  Fame run out its Date,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who snatch'd us from the Brink of Fate?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Else, why should Scholars, Sir, I pray,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Be Prisners on this glorious Day;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">When  Arms, by Heav'n's Decree,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Devoted it to Liberty?</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
